The Security Council: The Security Council is the most important and most powerful organ of the United Nations. It has 15 members, five permanent and 10 elected for two-year terms. The permanent members (China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom, and the United States) have veto power. This means that they can stop any decision of the Security Council, except a decision to use force.
The Security Council has three main functions.
1. It can make decisions about threats to the peace.
2. It can take action against these threats.
3. It can try to prevent conflict.
The Security Council has control over all
